The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their optimization through pruning. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of novel approaches in pruning, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different pruning signals, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) if the signals are related to natural language processing.
